text: Blanca Chan (born 26 July 1981) is a Mexican volleyball player. She played at the 2002 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship, 2003 Women's Pan-American Volleyball Cup, 2005 Women's NORCECA Volleyball Championship, 2006 Women's Pan-American Volleyball Cup, and 2006 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship. She played for Sinaloa. == References == Category:1981 births Category:Living people Category:Mexican volleyball players
